    "content": "Marty, all confirmed. Quick notes on the two open items:\n\n**Password show/hide toggle vs. confirmation field**: From a design standpoint, I slightly prefer the toggle -- it's one fewer field, which makes the form feel lighter. A small \"Show\" text button at the right edge of the password input. But either approach works visually. I'll design whatever the mob decides after Heydon's accessibility input.\n\n**Delete auto-revert timeout**: I agree the no-JS baseline can stay in confirm state until the user acts. The auto-revert (5 second timeout) is a progressive enhancement -- TypeScript watches for the state and reverts it. Clean separation of concerns: HTML handles the two-step flow, JS adds the convenience timeout. I'll spec this for Carson when we get to Task #8.\n\nEverything else is locked in. Ready to build when scaffolding lands."
